  </header>

  <main class="main-content">
    <article class="career-article">

      <section class="career-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">1. Professional Cricketer</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          Becoming a professional cricketer is the dream of many. With dedication, rigorous training, and performance in domestic and international formats, players can join national teams, leagues like the IPL, BBL, or The Hundred, and represent their countries globally.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="career-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">2. Cricket Coach</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          Coaches play a vital role in grooming talent at school, state, national, and franchise levels. Certification from institutions like the National Cricket Academy (NCA) or ICC is essential to pursue this path professionally.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="career-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">3. Umpire & Match Referee</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          If you have a sharp eye for the rules, consider officiating matches. Umpires and referees ensure the game is played fairly and within ICC laws. Training and certification from recognized cricket boards is mandatory.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="career-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">4. Sports Analyst / Commentator</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          Passionate about cricket stats, trends, and game breakdowns? A career as a sports analyst or commentator can combine your love of the game with media and journalism. Strong communication skills and game knowledge are crucial.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="career-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">5. Physiotherapist / Sports Psychologist</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          Support roles such as physiotherapists and psychologists help cricketers stay in peak physical and mental condition. Degrees in physiotherapy or sports psychology are typically required to enter this field.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="career-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">6. Groundsman / Equipment Manager</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          Behind every great match is a well-prepared pitch and perfectly managed equipment. These roles require practical training and a keen understanding of cricket infrastructure and logistics.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="career-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">7. Cricket Journalism & Content Creation</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          Write for cricket magazines, websites, or manage social media for players or teams. This path is ideal for storytellers who love the sport and want to share its excitement with the world.
        </p>
      </section>

    </article>
